Logic-TruthTable, version 1.00, 2 December 2016
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A structure to hold a Boolean truth table. Provides utility functions
to create or manipulate the minterms or maxterms of the table columns,
and makes use of the appropriate Algorithm modules for solving equations.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Build.PL
	Build
	Build test
	Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Logic::TruthTable

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Logic-TruthTable

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Logic-TruthTable

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Logic-TruthTable

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Logic-TruthTable/


